Title : Gorges du Guiers Vif
Text : The '''Gorges du Guiers Vif''' (or '''Gorges du Frou''') is a [[canyon]] located in [[Isère]] and [[Savoie]] between the towns of [[Corbel, Savoie|Corbel]] and [[Saint-Christophe-sur-Guiers]], and having as tributary the [[Guiers Vif]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.isere-tourisme.com/patrimoine-naturel/gorges-du-guiers-vif|title=Gorges du Guiers Vif|publisher=isere-tourisme.com|date= |accessdate=March 6, 2016}}</ref>

==Transportation==
In 1994 a little road was built that directly connects [[Saint-Pierre-d'Entremont (Savoie)|Saint-Pierre-d'Entremont in Savoie]] to [[Corbel, Savoie|Corbel]].  It passes through the ''Gorges du Guiers Vif''. However for driving people, it is reserved to the residents.

